name: 3',5'-nucleoside bisphosphate phosphatase
comment: The enzyme, characterized from the bacterium Chromobacterium violaceum, has similar catalytic efficiencies with all the bases. The enzyme has similar activity with ribonucleoside and 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphates, but shows no activity with nucleoside 2',5'-bisphosphates (cf. EC 3.1.3.7, 3'(2'),5'-bisphosphate nucleotidase).

references.title: Prospecting for unannotated enzymes: discovery of a 3',5'-nucleotide bisphosphate phosphatase within the amidohydrolase superfamily.
